The 2015 Eurasia Commodity and Trade Expo has opened in Urumqi, the capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. More than 20,000 businesses from 40 countries and regions have come to the expo, which lasts for five days. A total of 824 overseas companies are exhibiting at the event. The expo focuses on commodity exhibitions and trade and is held alternating years with the China-Eurasia Expo. The event is an important economic activity for Xinjiang, as it celebrates the 60th anniversary of its establishment as an autonomous region this year.



